> what  weight oil are you using?   I use a heavier oil in summer than
winter,
> but if it gets cool before the regular scheduled oil change the oil
pressure
> gets high, so I swap to a thinner oil.
>
> checker pressure relief valves is simple.   You shimmy under the engine,
and
> look for the one or two big screwed plugs under there- in dual relief one
is
> forward the other aft.  I put the vise grips on the real wide fat
screwdriver
> to undo them, and an oil bucker with help catch the drips and springs.
Not
> much oil comes out, but some does.  *-O
